column5: the day started real early   they were calling for low winds  and no rain so  we decided G bay would be our lake instead of  the Kawarthas  I used the free ramp in Midland and off we went   trolled for hours..stop a couple of times to tube for bass, but muskie was the fish of choice today...........the fish of how many casts....   we didn't catch any fish..didn't see any fish  but it was a great day on the water....................
Hey... you do that again without calling me and I'm gonna get them to tow your truck and trailer bud!
Nice pics - a lovely day for a boat ride!  :-)
Beautiful pics Terry!!!  Those trees look like they're on fire!
Wayne  it was a day that I had promised a guy I work with.........  but without a doubt...you can come with me any time you want.......

LOL Terry... just pullin your chain Bud. I just got back from Ottawa at 4:30PM !  Still ticked with myself though, that I never thought to take a fishing rod with me and then we spent all Friday afternoon on the side of the Rideau River and I could have fished the whole stretch below the Bronson St Bridge from shore.  Some beautiful colours in the trees that line GBay right now for sure.
some beautiful pictures of the trees!
Nice pictures Terry beautiful day to be on the water  Rob
Whats up with them colors? Man what diference from where I was today.

it was foggy first thing in the morning but just when the sun came out it hit the trees and looked great.............    and of course.....things light up when I am around......          LOL .... ok I couldn't finish typing that with a strait face
Well you couldn't have picked a better day to get skunked Terry  Beautiful panoramics there.  Joey
Great pics Terry Certainly was a beauti day to be out on the water  Leechman
Can't win em all but at least you got out there, nice pic's, thanks...
nice day to be on the water great pictures
Beauty pics Terry.  It was sure a nice weekend to be out on the water.
